<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="396" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Pruyn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 41.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in
                                        Japan</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Yokohama</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-06-24"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 24, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> British indemnity paid. United States
                            legation buildings at Yedo destroyed by fire on the 24th ultimo. Letters
                            received by treaty powers demanding their withdrawal, pursuant to orders
                            of Mikado and Tycoon from Kioto.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, sir, very respectfully, your most obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>ROBERT H. PRUYN, <hi rend="italic">Minister Resident in
                                    Japan.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington.</hi></p>
                            <p>(Above despatch sent to collector, San Francisco, to be
                                telegraphed.)</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>